FBIS3-60348 "jpten002__l94006" JPRS-TEN-94-002-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Environmental Issues 25 January 1994 EAST ASIA JAPAN Japan Environmental News Update (1-15 September 1993) Initial Requests for Budget Related to Global Environmental Protection Increases 946C3801F Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 7 Sep 93 p 5--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY 946C3801F Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Language: Japanese Article Type:CSO [Complete text of article obtained through NIKKEI BIZ DATABASE] [Text] The Environment Ministry summarized the initial requests for the FY94 budget for global environmental protection made by 17 ministries and agencies, including the Environment Agency, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, and the Science and Technology Agency. The total amount requested is 짜566.2 billion, an increase of 짜31.8 billion and 6 percent over FY93's actual budget. Concerning individual items, at 짜445.7 billion, the largest amount requested is for the "Development and Spread of Technologies for Global Environmental Protection," an increase of 3 percent over the previous year. The "Promotion of the Development and Use of Nuclear Energy" (Science and Technology Agency) is requesting 짜276.35 billion. Newly requested items include the "Establishment of Technological Standards for Gas Stations for Low-Pollution Vehicles" and a "Safety Study for a Sulfur Sodium Battery," both by the Ministry of Home Affairs.
